									"text" : "Resynthesis stage",
									"textcolor" : [ 0.501961, 0.501961, 0.501961, 1.0 ]
								}

							}
, 							{
								"box" : 								{
									"fontname" : "Arial",
									"fontsize" : 13.914225,
									"frgb" : [ 0.501961, 0.501961, 0.501961, 1.0 ],
									"id" : "obj-10",
									"maxclass" : "comment",
									"numinlets" : 1,
									"numoutlets" : 0,
									"patching_rect" : [ 208.0, 293.0, 99.0, 22.0 ],
									"text" : "Analysis stage",
									"textcolor" : [ 0.501961, 0.501961, 0.501961, 1.0 ]
								}

							}
, 							{
								"box" : 								{
									"fontname" : "Arial",
									"fontsize" : 11.595187,
									"frgb" : [ 0.501961, 0.501961, 0.501961, 1.0 ],
									"id" : "obj-9",
									"maxclass" : "comment",
									"numinlets" : 1,
									"numoutlets" : 0,
									"patching_rect" : [ 79.0, 272.0, 228.0, 20.0 ],
									"text" : "Viewed graphically, it's something like this:",
									"textcolor" : [ 0.501961, 0.501961, 0.501961, 1.0 ]
								}

							}
, 							{
								"box" : 								{
									"fontname" : "Arial",
									"fontsize" : 11.595187,
									"frgb" : [ 0.501961, 0.501961, 0.501961, 1.0 ],
									"id" : "obj-6",
									"linecount" : 3,
									"maxclass" : "comment",
									"numinlets" : 1,
									"numoutlets" : 0,
									"patching_rect" : [ 110.0, 223.0, 440.0, 46.0 ],
									"text" : "b) the resynthesis source sound is bandpass filtered using the same coefficients that were used in the analysis stage. The output of the avg~ object then determines the amplitude at which each band of the resynthesis source sound is played.",
									"textcolor" : [ 0.501961, 0.501961, 0.501961, 1.0 ]
								}

							}
, 							{
								"box" : 								{
									"fontname" : "Arial",
									"fontsize" : 11.595187,
									"frgb" : [ 0.501961, 0.501961, 0.501961, 1.0 ],
									"id" : "obj-7",
									"linecount" : 2,
									"maxclass" : "comment",
									"numinlets" : 1,
									"numoutlets" : 0,
									"patching_rect" : [ 110.0, 191.0, 448.0, 33.0 ],
									"text" : "a) if the incoming audio is determined to be a consonant, noise is sent as the resynthesis source sound. Otherwise, a pulse train is sent (to produce vowel sounds).",
									"textcolor" : [ 0.501961, 0.501961, 0.501961, 1.0 ]
								}

							}
, 							{
								"box" : 								{
									"fontname" : "Arial",
									"fontsize" : 11.595187,
									"frgb" : [ 0.501961, 0.501961, 0.501961, 1.0 ],
									"id" : "obj-8",
									"maxclass" : "comment",
									"numinlets" : 1,
									"numoutlets" : 0,
									"patching_rect" : [ 94.0, 171.0, 139.0, 20.0 ],
									"text" : "2. The resynthesis stage:",
									"textcolor" : [ 0.501961, 0.501961, 0.501961, 1.0 ]
								}

							}
, 							{
								"box" : 								{
									"fontname" : "Arial",
									"fontsize" : 11.595187,
									"frgb" : [ 0.501961, 0.501961, 0.501961, 1.0 ],
									"id" : "obj-5",
									"linecount" : 3,
									"maxclass" : "comment",
									"numinlets" : 1,
									"numoutlets" : 0,
									"patching_rect" : [ 110.0, 125.0, 454.0, 46.0 ],
									"text" : "b) how much signal energy is present at each of 15 frequency bands. Each channel~ abstraction contains a bandpass filter (reson~) tuned to a specific frequency, followed by an avg~ object to approximate how much signal energy is present at that frequency.",
									"textcolor" : [ 0.501961, 0.501961, 0.501961, 1.0 ]
								}

							}
, 							{
								"box" : 								{
									"fontname" : "Arial",
									"fontsize" : 11.595187,
									"frgb" : [ 0.501961, 0.501961, 0.501961, 1.0 ],
									"id" : "obj-4",
									"linecount" : 3,
									"maxclass" : "comment",
									"numinlets" : 1,
									"numoutlets" : 0,
									"patching_rect" : [ 110.0, 79.0, 397.0, 46.0 ],
									"text" : "a) whether the spoken sound is a consonant or a vowel. It does this using Richard Dudas's zerox~\tobject to count how many times the signal crosses the zero volt line (more crossings = noisier signal, therefore a consonant)",
									"textcolor" : [ 0.501961, 0.501961, 0.501961, 1.0 ]
								}

							}
, 							{
								"box" : 								{
									"fontname" : "Arial",
									"fontsize" : 11.595187,
									"frgb" : [ 0.501961, 0.501961, 0.501961, 1.0 ],
									"id" : "obj-3",
									"maxclass" : "comment",
									"numinlets" : 1,
									"numoutlets" : 0,
									"patching_rect" : [ 94.0, 59.0, 332.0, 20.0 ],
									"text" : "1. The analysis stage. It analyzes the incoming audio to detect:",
									"textcolor" : [ 0.501961, 0.501961, 0.501961, 1.0 ]
								}

							}
, 							{
								"box" : 								{
									"fontname" : "Arial",
									"fontsize" : 11.595187,
									"frgb" : [ 0.501961, 0.501961, 0.501961, 1.0 ],
									"id" : "obj-2",
									"maxclass" : "comment",
									"numinlets" : 1,
									"numoutlets" : 0,
									"patching_rect" : [ 79.0, 39.0, 137.0, 20.0 ],
									"text" : "It operates in two stages:",
									"textcolor" : [ 0.501961, 0.501961, 0.501961, 1.0 ]
								}

							}
, 							{
								"box" : 								{
									"fontname" : "Arial",
									"fontsize" : 11.595187,
									"frgb" : [ 0.501961, 0.501961, 0.501961, 1.0 ],
									"id" : "obj-1",
									"linecount" : 2,
									"maxclass" : "comment",
									"numinlets" : 1,
									"numoutlets" : 0,
									"patching_rect" : [ 79.0, 6.0, 468.0, 33.0 ],
									"text" : "This patch emulates the Moog vocoders from the 60's and 70's. Feed it speech input and compare the output with the robot voices in old reruns of \"Star Trek\" or \"Lost in Space\"",
									"textcolor" : [ 0.501961, 0.501961, 0.501961, 1.0 ]
								}

							}
 ],
